            },
            {
              "id": "m364",
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Shannon defined information entropy as H = -Σ p(x) log p(x). The key insight: information content is inversely related to probability. A rare event carries more information than a common one.\n\nThis connects to thermodynamic entropy — a deep link between physics and communication theory that most engineers never explore.",
              "x": 16,
              "y": 36,
              "width": 326,
              "height": 148,
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width-height",
              "fontSize": 12,
              "fontWeight": "400",
